  "subject": "Fix thread-safety race condition in AAIObjectMapper",
  "commit_message": "Fix thread-safety race condition in AAIObjectMapper\n\nMove all ModelMapper addMappings() calls from lazy-init inside\neach mapping method into the constructor. The previous pattern\nused a non-atomic check-then-act (getTypeMap==null -> addMappings)\nwhich throws ConfigurationException when two Camunda executor\nthreads call the same mapping method concurrently.\n\nSince AAIObjectMapper is a Spring @Component singleton, mappings\nare static configuration that should be registered exactly once\nat construction time.\n\nAdd concurrency tests that verify thread-safe operation with\n10 parallel threads calling mapServiceInstance and mapVnf.\n\nIssue-ID: SO-4355\nSigned-off-by: Fiete Ostkamp <fiete.ostkamp@telekom.de>\nChange-Id: I328b5f80817121b09b08c83e8f97513a7430bda8\n",
